        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We wish maximize the continuum sensitivity, but the search of molecular outflow is needed for verifying the nature of the object. Therefore 3+1. We will average CO(3-2) channels during post-processing, because the data rate is not a problem here. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The central source is unresolved at a resolution of 3.6 arcsec. Our goal is to determine the disk size or an upper limit for it. According to some models, Class 0 disk radii are maximally a few tens of AU, according to others, the disks reach in a short time radii of 50-100 AU . The requested angular resolution 0.2 arcsec corresponds to 30 AU at the distance of the source (150 pc). We will be therefore able to obtain a very meaningful upper limit of 15 AU for the disk radius if the object is unresolved. 

 </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The flux density of the central source is 2.3 mJy at 106 GHz (Mardones et al., ALMA Cycle 1 project 2012.1.00394.S), and it is unresolved with the 3.6 arcsec beam. Assuming modifed blackbody with beta=1, and that the source fills uniformly the 3.6 arcsec beam, we estimate that the intensity at 0.87 mm is 0.2 mJy/0.2 arcsec beam. This is a conservative  estimate because almost certainly there is substructure within 3". However, to ensure a S/N of 5 in the map we request a sensitivity of 40 micro Jy/beam, which should be reached in about 2 hours. In this time we will reach a sensitivity in CO(3-2) which is adequate for detecting the outflow. Here we can smooth the map to a 0.5 arcsec resolution after which the rms noise will be 0.1 K per 1 km/s velocity channel.   </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
